sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641220
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence has two primer sites and a restriction enzyme site between FRT and loxP for further testing in our experiment. Two primers are: GCACCTTGACTCTGACAATCCT (forward) GCCTGTGCTAATGGTGATGACT (reverse) they both have a high annealing temperature (about 58C). They can be used as qPCR primers. The restriction enzyme sites are HindIII and BanI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianheng Liu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641213
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A qPCR friendly short terminator BBa_B1006 was inserted after mCherry。
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianheng Liu & Yingnan Niu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J44002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the pBAD promoter (BBa_I13453) in the opposite orientation. It can be used to drive transcription in the direction of suffix to prefix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brad Ogden

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641211
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Flpe recombinase BBa_K313002 with strong RBS(BBa_B0034) and ssrA tag(BBa_M0051), which can be translated strongly and eliminated in a short time if the flpe is not expressed continuely.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianheng Liu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding for Cre recombinase with ssrA tag. It can express Cre in high level and can be fast degraded if promoter is turned off.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianheng Liu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ECFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: enhanced cyan fluorescent protein derived from A. victoria GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Cyan fluorescent protein (ECFP) reporter coding sequence without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_E0022 cyan fluorescent protein is based on BioBrick part BBa_E0021. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641222
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Flpe recombinase with ssrA tag(BBa_M0051). Stop codon TAATAA was added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianheng Liu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1641223
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Cre recombinase wit ssrA tag（BBa_M0051）. Stop codons TAATAA were added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianheng Liu
